  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  women with PCOS diagnosed in accordance with Rotterdam Consensus Conference Criteria
             2003

          -  BMI &gt; 25 kg/m2

          -  age 18-35 years

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  pregnancy

          -  significant liver or renal impairment

          -  other hormonal dysfunctions (hypothalamic, pituitary, thyroidal or adrenal causes for
             the clinical signs)

          -  neoplasms

          -  unstable mental illness

          -  diagnosis of diabetes mellitus or impaired glucose tolerance

          -  use of drugs able to interfere with gluco-insulinaemic metabolism for at least three
             months prior entering the study.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
